Mushroom pies are a type of pie that can be obtained by baking an uncooked mushroom pie on a cooking range, requiring level 60 Cooking and granting 200 experience when successful. Players may burn the pie while baking one, resulting in a burnt pie; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 89 on ranges. Alternatively, casting the Bake Pie spell from the lunar spellbook guarantees successful baking of all pies.

Mushroom pie heals 16 Hitpoints in total, 2 bites each healing 8, and grants a temporary skill boost to Crafting by 4 levels, the second highest available. However, this is a reliable boost, unlike orange spicy stew, which provides a random boost between a -5 and 5 when 3 orange spices are added. After eating it, a pie dish will remain.

Steps
1. Use a pastry dough on a pie dish to make a pie shell
2. Use a sulliuscep cap on the pie shell to make a uncooked mushroom pie
3. Cook the uncooked mushroom pie on a range to finish a mushroom pie

'''Mushroom pies''' are a type of [[pie]] that can be obtained by baking an [[uncooked mushroom pie]] on a [[cooking range]], requiring level 60 [[Cooking]] and granting 200 experience when successful. Players may burn the pie while baking one, resulting in a [[burnt pie]]; the [[burn rate]] while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at [[Cooking]] level 89 on ranges. Alternatively, casting the [[Bake Pie]] spell from the [[lunar spellbook]] guarantees successful baking of all pies.

Mushroom pie heals 16 [[Hitpoints]] in total, 2 bites each healing 8, and grants a [[temporary skill boost]] to [[Crafting]] by 4 levels, the second highest available. However, this is a reliable boost, unlike orange [[spicy stew]], which provides a random boost between a -5 and 5 when 3 orange spices are added. After eating it, a [[pie dish]] will remain.
